---
description: GraphQL resolvers must not access databases directly
globs: firebase/functions/src/Graphql/**/*.ts
alwaysApply: false
---

# GraphQL Resolver DB Boundary

- Do not import `Data/*` database modules in resolver files for query execution.
- Importing `Data/*` types/enums for typing is allowed; executing queries is not.
- Resolver data access must go through service methods and the dataloaders on `GraphqlRequestContext`.

## Allowed

```typescript
const project = await projectService.getProjectByIdOrThrow({ projectId: id })
const user = await context.userDataloader.load(project.createdByUserId)
```

## Avoid

```typescript
const project = await projectDb.query.projectsTable.findFirst({ where: eq(projectsTable.id, id) })
```
